{% from 'macros.njk' import insertNote %}
<p>Some facts about me:</p>

<ol>
    <li>I write code. Sometimes for money, sometimes for fun.</li>
    <li>I have a poor working memory. {{ insertNote(text = "I have pretty severe ADHD. I'm medicated, but meds can only do so much.") }}</li>
    <li>I tend to use a relatively small, but consistent set of tools.</li>
</ol>

<p>To compensate for my working memory deficiencies, I often try to <mark>externalize information</mark>. This is one such attempt to do so.</p>

<h1>crib sheets</h1>
<ul>
{% for item in collections.crib %}
    <li><a href="{{ item.url }}">{{ item.data.title or item.page.fileSlug }}</a></li>
{% endfor %}
</ul>

<h1>notes</h1>
<ul>
{% for item in collections.notes %}
    <li><a href="{{ item.url }}">{{ item.data.title or item.page.fileSlug }}</a></li>
{% endfor %}
</ul>

<h1>snippets</h1>
<ul>
{% for item in collections.snippets %}
    <li><a href="{{ item.url }}">{{ item.data.title or item.page.fileSlug }}</a></li>
{% endfor %}
</ul>